[h1] An alternative to Rainmeter [/h1] 

It is more user-friendly, and graphically nicer! Although, it may not be for everyone as it's an anime-focused widget app. You can still make some workarounds but it will need some time.

The paid option is for workshop access and it's not that bad, got to support the devs.

Great replacement for rainmeter honestly, Also the beta/the workshop is very cheap which is a plus. 
I really like the overlay/launcher menu thingy. Such a great way to have for your desktop enhancement. I don't use the widgets for the desktop because i like to keep it clean but it's also good if you are the kind of person that like seeing hud on your desktop.

I hope for more update and more templates/workshop content to be shared 10/10

It's not exactly as customizable as rainmeter unless you go deep down into the rabbithole, but even still with the customization that it DOES have, you can make some pretty slick looking setups. And I would like to note that it is SIGNIFICANTLY more lightweight than rainmeter and rocketdock. 

All in all, I prefer to use this over rainmeter and rocketdock. It's clean, customizable enough for me, and offers exactly what I wanted in a lightweight platform.

-Design are vast you just need some time to learn about the widgets because workshop does't have too much to give but soon when more themes and widgets available it will be the best better than windows system. my problem right now is how can i replay the task bar so i can fully clean my desktop and replace with this application.
-the Developer is also very active so no need to be afraid to ask or suggest about more ideas.
-just telling you yes it is a base on SAO but someone already upload genshin impact theme and i know more are coming soon.

this app is really something else. although i barley have a few dozen hours on this game i can assure its worth every cent. the freedom and the infinite possibilities that are provided here are truly amazing. as a sword art online fan i really am proud to be able to call myself a beta tester of this software and get access to such amazing features that allows your pc to be infinitly cooler and easier to use. the only downside of this app is that there isn't any good tutorial to explain the basics that are pretty easy to understand, and specially when the thing you are trying to achieve get more complicated, but for me it was experience, after alot of fails and successes i slowly but surly i got the hang of it and now understand to pretty much do anything my heart desires. now about the achievement i finally got it and proud to have 3/4 achievements. the only one left is becoming a "SAO SURVIVOR". i dont really know what i need to do to complete it but i guess i will when the time comes to it, the rest of the achievements are pretty easy to get,  you just have to log out from the menu to get the "beta tester". and the rest i just got randomly. anyway thanks for taking your time and read this message.  i wish you the best of luck with whatever challenges may come ahead, my fellow SAO survivors ;D

Everything about this is fantastic! I paid for the Beta, and I am glad I did!

Customising the user interface is easy! Too easy that I got a complete working overlay working in just under 4 hours of tinkering for the first time! (much quicker if you know what you are doing, I'd say around it will take 80% less time than first-time-usage!)

There's a workshop you can download many assets from, although, at the time of doing this review, there isn't much that catches my fancy yet, maybe the BOTW asset packs.

Overall, compared to the previous Beta Version, This is a HUGE step up to being a great piece of software!

Also, don't check my hours in SAO Utils: Beta.
